Many adults who endured violence while growing up have had to deal with a broad spectrum of childhood traumas.Teenhood comes with a deep exploration of boundaries, thoughts, ideas, perceptions and experiences, which eventually helps in the growth of a teen. There’s a generation that was raised in households that silenced and punished teenhood out of them. Their expressions and desires were completely shut down.
This out-of-the-norm existence that teenagers naturally pursue is what is falsely interpreted as improper behaviour and is thus punished out of them. Additionally, teens are constantly reminded of not knowing anything and spoken to in a tone that reminds them how awful they are.



